pre-excitation is suspected. Genetic testing is useful where a clear

diagnosis is established or the pre-test probability is high, such that a

positive test will influence the management not only of the patient but of

their family. Cardiac biopsy may have a role in diagnosing inflammatory

or infiltrative diseases, such as myocarditis or sarcoidosis, but is

increasingly less used with the advent of advanced imaging modalities,

such as cMRI and PET-CT, which we only perform when the imaging

findings are in doubt in cases of suspected sarcoidosis.

